[Event "Scholar's Mate and Its Refutation"]
[Result "*"]

{Scholar's Mate is the most common trap beginners fall into. Learn to spot it and punish it.} 1. e4 e5 2. Bc4 {Aiming at f7 early.} (2. Qh5?! {The crude queen attack — easy to refute.} Nc6 3. Bc4 g6! {Kicking the queen away and developing.} 4. Qf3 Nf6 {Black is already better developed.}) Nc6 (2... Bc5 {Also fine — developing and controlling the center.}) 3. Qh5 {Here comes the threat: Qxf7#.} Nf6! {The only good move — developing and attacking the queen.} (3... g6?? {The blunder!} 4. Qxf7# {Scholar's Mate. Game over.}) (3... Qe7 {Playable but passive.} 4. Nf3 Nf6 5. Qh4 {White keeps the pressure.}) 4. Qf3 {Retreating, but still eyeing f7.} (4. Qe2 {A tame retreat.} d5! {Black seizes the center.}) d5! {Striking in the center with tempo.} 5. exd5 Nd4! {A strong knight jump — threatening Nxc2+ and attacking the queen.} 6. Qd1 (6. Qd3 Nxc2+ {Winning the rook.}) Bg4! {Pinning the queen's escape route. Black has a dominant position out of the opening.} *
